---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'

const title = 'Affiliate Disclosure'
const description =
  'How GHS Pictograms participates in affiliate programs, how affiliate links are marked, and why our editorial content stays independent of commission.'
const canonical = 'https://ghspictograms.com/affiliate-disclosure/'

export const prerender = true
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-10">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="text-[#062A78] hover:underline">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">→</span>
      <span class="text-gray-700">Affiliate Disclosure</span>
    </nav>

    <h1
      class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight"
      style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif"
    >
      Affiliate Disclosure
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-lg">
      How we participate in affiliate programs, how we mark affiliate links, and why our
      editorial content remains independent of commission.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: 23 June 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">
          How affiliate relationships work
        </h2>
        <p>
          GHS Pictograms (ghspictograms.com) is an independent reference for GHS hazard
          classification and chemical safety compliance, operated from Riga, Latvia. We
          participate in affiliate programs with selected providers of SDS authoring and
          management software and adjacent chemical-compliance services. When a reader clicks
          an affiliate link from our pages and subsequently makes a purchase or subscribes, we
          may earn a commission at no additional cost to the reader.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Affiliate commissions help fund our independent content. They do not determine which
          tools or services we cover, how we describe them, or what we recommend.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">
          How affiliate links are marked
        </h2>
        <p>Every outbound affiliate link on this site carries two visible signals plus two technical signals:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li>A dagger symbol (&dagger;) appears immediately next to the link text.</li>
          <li>Pages containing affiliate links display an affiliate disclosure note.</li>
          <li>The HTML attribute <code class="text-sm bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">rel="sponsored nofollow noopener"</code> is applied to every affiliate link, in line with Google's webmaster guidelines.</li>
          <li>Affiliate links open in a new tab via <code class="text-sm bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">target="_blank"</code>.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If a link does not show a dagger and is not on a page with an affiliate disclosure, it
          is not an affiliate link.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">
          Active affiliate programs
        </h2>
        <p>
          This section lists every active partnership as it goes live, along with the date the
          partnership began.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 font-semibold text-gray-900">Currently active</p>
        <div class="mt-2 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900">
            SDS Manager (sdsmanager.com)
          </p>
          <p class="mt-1">
            SDS authoring and management software, plus an adjacent EHS suite. We participate
            in SDS Manager's affiliate program and may earn a recurring commission when a reader
            subscribes through our link, at no additional cost to the reader. SDS Manager is a
            third-party partner; it is a solution we recommend, not a product we operate.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500">Active since 22 June 2026.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">
          Editorial independence
        </h2>
        <p>
          Our compliance content, comparisons, and tool descriptions are written before any
          affiliate decision is made. We frequently describe and recommend tools and services
          for which we receive no commission, when they are the right fit for the reader.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We do not write articles or descriptions in exchange for commission, payment, or
          product. Where a provider has paid for a featured or sponsored placement, that
          placement is clearly labelled <span class="font-semibold">Sponsored</span> and kept
          separate from editorial content. There is no sponsored content on this site at present.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may decline to recommend an affiliate partner if our editorial evaluation finds the
          product unsuitable for our readers, regardless of commission terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">
          Editor's commitment
        </h2>
        <p>
          If an affiliate partner's product no longer meets our editorial standard, we remove the
          affiliate placement before we change what we say about it. Commission never overrides
          accuracy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">
          Compliance with disclosure laws
        </h2>
        <p>This disclosure is intended to satisfy material-connection requirements under:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li><span class="font-semibold">United States:</span> FTC 16 CFR Part 255 — Guides Concerning the Use of Endorsements and Testimonials in Advertising.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold">United Kingdom:</span> CAP Code Rule 2.4 — commercial intent must be obvious.</li>
          <li><span class="font-semibold">European Union:</span> Unfair Commercial Practices Directive 2005/29/EC, Article 7(2) — hidden commercial intent is a misleading practice.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#062A78] mb-3" style="font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif">
          Questions
        </h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about our affiliate relationships or editorial process, contact us
          at <a href="mailto:sergejssevcenko@ghslabels.com" class="text-[#062A78] font-semibold hover:underline">sergejssevcenko@ghslabels.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
        This disclosure was last updated on 23 June 2026 and may be revised as our affiliate
        programs change.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
